                                    <watches>1</watches>
                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14263260" author="britter" created="Fri, 2 Jan 2015 21:55:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If it&apos;s not in the IANA list of TLDs, than it is not correct IMHO.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14263298" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Fri, 2 Jan 2015 22:48:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In that case, we should also remove &quot;um&quot; and &quot;yu&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;They are not in the file &lt;a href=&quot;http://data.iana.org/TLD/tlds-alpha-by-domain.txt&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://data.iana.org/TLD/tlds-alpha-by-domain.txt&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However they are listed in &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.iana.org/domains/root/db&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.iana.org/domains/root/db&lt;/a&gt; as &quot;Not assigned&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There are lots of other such country codes which are in the HTML version but not the text version.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;root&quot; is not in either of the above, though AFAIK it does have a single DNS entry, viz. vrsn-end-of-zone-marker-dummy-record.root&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14264007" author="sebb@apache.org" created="Sun, 4 Jan 2015 21:05:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;URL: &lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/r1649419&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/r1649419&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Log:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/VALIDATOR-350&quot; title=&quot;Should &amp;quot;x.root&amp;quot; validate as a domain name?&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;VALIDATOR-350&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;VALIDATOR-350&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; - Should &quot;x.root&quot; validate as a domain name?&lt;br/&gt;
Removed &quot;root&quot; from TLD list.&lt;br/&gt;
Also &quot;um&quot; and &quot;yu&quot; as they are currently &quot;Not assigned&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Modified:&lt;br/&gt;
    commons/proper/validator/trunk/RELEASE-NOTES.txt&lt;br/&gt;
    commons/proper/validator/trunk/src/changes/changes.xml&lt;br/&gt;
    commons/proper/validator/trunk/src/main/java/org/apache/commons/validator/routines/DomainValidator.java&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
